</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Rudolph_Bergh_Buste.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b7/Rudolph_Bergh_Buste.jpg/220px-Rudolph_Bergh_Buste.jpg" decoding="async" width="220" height="293" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b7/Rudolph_Bergh_Buste.jpg/330px-Rudolph_Bergh_Buste.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b7/Rudolph_Bergh_Buste.jpg/440px-Rudolph_Bergh_Buste.jpg 2x" data-file-width="1944" data-file-height="2592" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Rudolph_Bergh_Buste.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Bust of Rudolph Bergh made by <a href="/wiki/Peder_Severin_Kr%C3%B8yer" title="Peder Severin Krøyer">Peder Severin Krøyer</a> is in <a href="/wiki/Copenhagen" title="Copenhagen">Copenhagen</a>.</div></div></div>
<p><b>Rudolph Bergh</b> (15 October 1824 – 20 July 1909), full name <b>Ludvig Sophus Rudolph Bergh</b>, was a <a href="/wiki/Denmark" title="Denmark">Danish</a> <a href="/wiki/Physician" title="Physician">physician</a> and <a href="/wiki/Malacologist" class="mw-redirect" title="Malacologist">malacologist</a>. He worked in <a href="/wiki/Copenhagen" title="Copenhagen">Copenhagen</a>.
</p><p>As a doctor his speciality was <a href="/wiki/Sexually_transmitted_disease" class="mw-redirect" title="Sexually transmitted disease">sexually transmitted diseases</a>. In Copenhagen a hospital and a street are named after him.
</p><p>Bergh was also an active malacologist, i.e. a <a href="/wiki/Zoologist" class="mw-redirect" title="Zoologist">zoologist</a> who studies molluscs, in particular the <a href="/wiki/Nudibranch" title="Nudibranch">nudibranchs</a>, shell-less <a href="/wiki/Marine_(ocean)" class="mw-redirect" title="Marine (ocean)">marine</a> <a href="/wiki/Gastropod" class="mw-redirect" title="Gastropod">gastropods</a>. He had well over 90 publications in this field and took part in a scientific expedition to <a href="/wiki/Indonesia" title="Indonesia">Indonesia</a>. He named and described numerous species of nudibranchs.
</p>
